results.name: Decimal expansion of (7/120)*Pi^4 = (21/4)*zeta(4).
comment: Equals Integral_{0..infinity} x^3/(exp(x) + 1) dx = (7/120)*Pi^4 = (21/4)*A013662. (Fermi-Dirac). See Abramowitz-Stegun, 23.2.8, for s=4, p. 807, and Landau-Lifschitz, eq. (1), for x=4, p. 172.
reference: L. D. Landau and E. M. Lifschitz, Band V, Statistische Physik, Akademie Verlag, 1966, eq. (1) for x=4, p. 172.
link: M. Abramowitz and I. A. Stegun, eds., Handbook of Mathematical Functions, National Bureau of Standards, Applied Math. Series 55, Tenth Printing, 1972 [alternative scanned copy].
results.author: _Wolfdieter Lang_, Sep 16 2020
